org.spongepowered.api.plugin

Annotation Type Plugin


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Plugin
    An annotation used to describe and mark a Sponge plugin.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Fields and Description
      static Pattern ID_PATTERN
      The pattern plugin IDs must match.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description

      An ID for the plugin to be used internally.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description

      The dependencies required to load before this plugin.
      String description
      The description of the plugin, explaining what it can be used for.

      String url

      String version
      The version of the plugin.

    • Field Detail

      • ID_PATTERN

        public static final Pattern ID_PATTERN
        The pattern plugin IDs must match. Plugin IDs must be lower case, and start with an alphabetic character. It may only contain alphanumeric characters, dashes or underscores. It cannot be longer than 64 characters.

    • Element Detail

      • id

        public abstract String id
        An ID for the plugin to be used internally. The ID should be unique as to not conflict with other plugins.

        The plugin ID must match the ID_PATTERN.

        Returns:
        The plugin identifier
        See Also:
        Java package naming conventions
